		<td><b>Re: puNES Emulator</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Two issues that hopefully may be addressed in future releases, currently utilizing 0.102 and happening under both the SDL and D3D versions:<br /><br />1.  Overscan cropping is applied after incorporating a shader effect; instead, it should be applied before the shader implementation.<br />For example, utilizing the shader 'CRT with curve', when Overscan is turned Off, the corners of the screen are round.  However, when Overscan is turned On, the round corners of the screen are cropped out and pointed screen corners remain.<br /><br />2.  Software Filters &quot;NTSC XXXXXXX&quot; shrink the width of the screen; rather, the same screen size/width should be maintained.<br />The narrowing of the screen occurs in a window, but even more severely fullscreen.  It does not happen with the other Software Filters: Scale #X,  Hq#X, xBRZ #X, and xBRZ #X MT; they do not change the size/width of the display in either a window or fullscreen.  The narrowing screen width only happens with: NTSC Composite, NTSC S-Video, and NTSC RGB.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


